category: CONTRONYMS
category comment: (Ken: Those are words that can serve as their own antonyms.)

clue: It's the mildest type of burn but the harshest type of murder

response: first degree

clue: It can mean to attach something, like with a clasp, or to detach something, like coupons

response: clip

clue: If you get it on your food, it's a little bonus; if a court does it to your wages, it's anything but

response: garnish

clue: This adjective describes both something that moves quickly & something that doesn't move at all

response: fast

clue: It can mean to withstand something (a storm, for instance) as well as to erode under it

response: weather

